<item>
            <title>[LU-3425] update l_getgroups to be l_getidentity</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3425</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;l_getidentity Utility

  The l_getidentity utility handles the Lustre supplementary group upcall
  by default, as described in the preceding section.

SYNOPSIS

  l_getidentity {mdtname} {uid}

DESCRIPTION

   The identity upcall file...should complete the identity_downcall_data
   data structure ... 
   ... write it to the {{/proc/fs/lustre/mdt/$MDT/identity_info}} pseudo
   file.

   l_getidentity is the reference ...

FILES

   /proc/fs/lustre/mdt/$MDT/identity_upcall
   /proc/fs/lustre/mdt/$MDT/identity_info
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would also make sense to implement the &lt;tt&gt;&lt;del&gt;d|&lt;/del&gt;-debug&lt;/tt&gt; option as was available for the l_getgroups upcall, in addition to the wonky &lt;tt&gt;L_GETIDENTITY_TEST&lt;/tt&gt; environment variable.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
